<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.399573>
    dc:description "FIGURES 31 – 40. Physiphora alceae: 31, ♂ phallus (a — fragment of preglans, enlarged); 32, glans, enlarged; 33, epandrium, posterior; 34, same, anterior; 35 ♀, eversible membrane, ventral; 36, aculeus; 37, same, tip, enlarged; 38 – 39, vagina and ventral receptacle, lateral and ventral; 40, spermathecae. Figs. 32, 34 – 40, from Kameneva & Korneyev, 2010; Fig. 33, from Chen & Kameneva, 2007 (drawn by V. A. Korneyev)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/399573/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.399572>
    dc:description "FIGURES 28 – 30. Physiphora alceae: 28, ♀ habitus, left, photo by František Mucha (Slovakia); 29, head, anterior (UAE), from Kameneva & Korneyev, 2010: fig. 9; 30, head and mesonotum, dorsal (Ukraine)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/399572/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

